      • correctCASCheckSum

        public static boolean correctCASCheckSum(java.lang.String casNumber)
        This function is a simple CAS checksum checker. Enter a CASRN (with or without dashes) and either the test will pass or fail. Recall that a CASRN must be 5-7 digits - 2 digits - 1 digit and that the last digit is the checksum value.
        Parameters:
        casNumber - Enter a CASRN with or without dashes. The CASRN must be of type string.
        Returns:
        True if checksum passes, False if checksum fails.
